<section class="w-full py-24 md:py-32 px-6 md:px-12 lg:px-24 bg-[#f4f6f8]">
  <div class="max-w-[1200px] mx-auto">
    <div class="text-center mb-16 md:mb-20">
      <h2
        class="text-4xl md:text-5xl lg:text-6xl text-[#1e293b] tracking-tight leading-[1.1] mb-6"
        style="font-family: 'Playfair Display', serif;"
      >
        How the Wound Remembers
      </h2>
      <p
        class="text-[10px] md:text-[11px] font-bold tracking-[0.3em] text-[#3cbce6] uppercase"
      >
        What We See &middot; What We Hear &middot; What We Cannot Forget
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-6 md:gap-8">
      <div
        class="bg-white p-10 md:p-12 rounded-xl border border-slate-100 shadow-[0_2px_10px_-4px_rgba(0,0,0,0.05)]"
      >
        <svg
          xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
          class="w-8 h-8 text-[#3cbce6] mb-8"
          viewBox="0 0 24 24"
          fill="currentColor"
        >
          <path
            d="M12 4.5C7 4.5 2.73 7.61 1 12c1.73 4.39 6 7.5 11 7.5s9.27-3.11 11-7.5c-1.73-4.39-6-7.5-11-7.5zM12 17c-2.76 0-5-2.24-5-5s2.24-5 5-5 5 2.24 5 5-2.24 5-5 5zm0-8c-1.66 0-3 1.34-3 3s1.34 3 3 3 3-1.34 3-3-1.34-3-3-3z"
          ></path>
        </svg>
        <h3
          class="text-2xl md:text-[28px] text-[#1e293b] mb-4"
          style="font-family: 'Playfair Display', serif;"
        >
          What We See
        </h3>
        <p class="text-[#64748b] text-[15px] leading-[1.8] font-light">
          The eye is not drawn to what is bright — it is drawn to what is true.
          We strip away until only the irreducible remains. What you see in our
          work is not decoration. It is what survived after everything dishonest
          was taken away.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div
        class="bg-white p-10 md:p-12 rounded-xl border border-slate-100 shadow-[0_2px_10px_-4px_rgba(0,0,0,0.05)]"
      >
        <svg
          xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
          class="w-8 h-8 text-[#3cbce6] mb-8"
          viewBox="0 0 24 24"
          fill="currentColor"
        >
          <path
            d="M12 3v18m-4-14v10m8-10v10m-12-6v2m16-2v2"
            stroke="currentColor"
            stroke-width="2"
            stroke-linecap="round"
            stroke-linejoin="round"></path>
        </svg>
        <h3
          class="text-2xl md:text-[28px] text-[#1e293b] mb-4"
          style="font-family: 'Playfair Display', serif;"
        >
          What We Hear
        </h3>
        <p class="text-[#64748b] text-[15px] leading-[1.8] font-light">
          Silence is not empty. It is the space where what has already been said
          continues to echo. We design for that echo — for the moment after the
          noise stops, when the only thing left is what actually mattered.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div
        class="bg-white p-10 md:p-12 rounded-xl border border-slate-100 shadow-[0_2px_10px_-4px_rgba(0,0,0,0.05)]"
      >
        <svg
          xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
          class="w-8 h-8 text-[#3cbce6] mb-8"
          viewBox="0 0 24 24"
          fill="currentColor"
        >
          <path
            d="M21 10.5V17a8 8 0 01-14.7 4.29l-4.04-5.38a2 2 0 012.83-2.83l1.91 1.91V4a2 2 0 014 0v5.5a2 2 0 014 0v1.5a2 2 0 014 0v-0.5a2 2 0 014 0z"
          ></path>
        </svg>
        <h3
          class="text-2xl md:text-[28px] text-[#1e293b] mb-4"
          style="font-family: 'Playfair Display', serif;"
        >
          What We Cannot Forget
        </h3>
        <p class="text-[#64748b] text-[15px] leading-[1.8] font-light">
          Memory lives in texture. In the roughness of something that refused
          to be smoothed over. In the weight of a surface that has been touched
          too many times to pretend it is still new. We build things that carry
          their history — because only what has been worn can be trusted to last.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>